
 IBM GitHub Enterprise – GitHub Assistant Implementation Guide (Clean Version)

## 1. Key Differences: Public GitHub vs IBM GitHub Enterprise

| Aspect              | Public GitHub                 | IBM GitHub Enterprise               |
|---------------------|-------------------------------|------------------------------------ |
| Base URL            | `https://api.github.com`      | `https://github.ibm.com/api/v3`     |
| Authentication      | Optional for public repos     | Required                            |
| Repository Access   | Public repos                  | Internal IBM repos                  |
| Default Owner       | Any                           | `maximo-application-suite`          |




 2. OpenAPI Specification Changes

Update Server URL
```yaml
servers:
  - url: https://github.ibm.com/api/v3
    description: IBM GitHub Enterprise API Server
```

Add Authentication
```yaml
security:
  - githubToken: []
```

```yaml
components:
  securitySchemes:
    githubToken:
      type: http
      scheme: bearer
      bearerFormat: token
```

Lock Down Repository Owner

Hardcode owner:
```yaml
/repos/maximo-application-suite/{repo}/readme:
  parameters:
    - name: repo
      in: path
      required: true
```
Update API Info
```yaml
info:
  title: IBM MAS GitHub Documentation Reader API
  version: 2.0.0
```

Add Standard Error Responses
```yaml
responses:
  '200': { description: Success }
  '401': { description: Unauthorized }
  '403': { description: Forbidden }
  '404': { description: Not found }
```

---

3. IBM GitHub Enterprise Personal Access Token (PAT)

How to Generate
1. Go to `https://github.ibm.com`
2. Profile → Settings → Developer settings
3. Personal access tokens → Generate new token
4. Select scope: `repo`
5. Generate and copy token

Format
`ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx`

---

4. Watsonx Orchestrate Agent Configuration

Agent Description
- Fetches documentation from IBM GitHub Enterprise  
- Default repository: `maximo-application-suite/support`  
- Requires IBM GitHub Enterprise PAT  

Key Operations
- `getReadme`
- `readFile`
- `findDocumentationFiles`
- `searchInRepository`

Default Behavior
```
Use owner = "maximo-application-suite".
Use repo = "support" unless user specifies otherwise.
```

---

5. Adding the OpenAPI Tool in Orchestrate

1. Build → AI Model → Create Agent  
2. Toolset → Add Tool → OpenAPI  
3. Upload modified `openapi_spec.yaml`  
4. Configure authentication: Bearer Token → paste PAT  
5. Add all endpoints  

---

6. Guidelines for the Agent

Installation Requests
- Read README from `maximo-application-suite/support`
- If missing, check:
  - `docs/install.md`
  - `docs/installation.md`
  - `INSTALL.md`

Configuration Requests
Check in order:
1. `docs/configuration.md`
2. `docs/config.md`
3. `CONFIG.md`
4. README configuration section

Troubleshooting Requests
Check in order:
1. `docs/troubleshooting.md`
2. `docs/faq.md`
3. `TROUBLESHOOTING.md`

---

7. Testing Checklist

- Authentication works  
- Default repo is used  
- File reading works  
- Search works  
- Errors handled correctly  

---

8. Common Issues

### Common Issues

| Issue            | Cause                   | Fix                  |
|------------------|-------------------------|----------------------|
| 401 Unauthorized | Invalid/expired token   | Regenerate PAT       |
| 404 Not Found    | Wrong repo/owner        | Verify repo path     |
| 403 Forbidden    | Missing scopes          | Add `repo` scope     |
| Rate Limit       | Too many requests       | Wait/reset           |

---

9. Deployment & Maintenance

- Deploy after tests  
- Monitor authentication failures  
- Rotate PAT every 90 days  
- Update OpenAPI if GitHub API changes  

---
10. Security Requirements

- Never store PAT in code  
- Use minimal scopes  
- comply with IBM internal security policies  
